        <abstract> 
<p>CD wants Lepadidae drawings [for <hi rend="italic">Fossil Cirripedia</hi>] harder, with lines of growth more distinct; he wants no shading or similarity to lithography, which he thinks has harmed natural history. He realises that mutilated specimens may make accuracy difficult.</p> 
        </abstract>
